The '''black-ringed white-eye''' or '''lemon-throated white-eye''' ('''''Zosterops anomalus''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Zosteropidae]]. It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Sulawesi]], [[Indonesia]]. Its natural [[habitat]] is subtropical or tropical moist lowland [[forest]]s.
